rComments: Good prof funny

He powers through the questions in class, but will show you how to do any problem you have trouble with. Went to his office hours regularly and he went through the whole assignment with me, it moved my grade from a low B to an A- by the end of class.
Good Prof. Hard Course, but managable.

Great class, the professor has a very dry wit and seems to know a lot about the subject. There are a lot of readings and a lot of summaries, but it makes you to read the readings which are what the midterm and final are on.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Lecture slides reflect textbook chapter, so it's not mandatory to attend class. Prof goes over a lot of chapter problems in class. 30% of your grade comes from online quizzes which you have unlimited attempts on (however if you read the corresponding textbook chapter it is easy to get 100% on the quizzes). Lots of common knowledge facts are tested.

Don't take him for this class. It probably doesn't help that the course material is confusing. But he speed reads through his slides that are literally definitions and examples taken from the textbook. So you might as well just learn from the textbook.

Pretty funny. At times it feels as if he overcomplicates the material. Lectures are based on textbook (which was cheap thank god), however reading beforehand would be a pretty good idea to understand the material a bit more.

He has online quizzes that worth 30% of the course and you can do them as many times as you want (great for studying tools too) ! easy 100% right there. The textbook he uses is easy to follow and cheap, his lectures are basically an explanation of the chapters in there. He also provides a sheet of what will be on the midterm/exam and it is accurate
Great professor, does lots of examples until the entire class understands a topic.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: One of the worst profs i've had in four years of undergrad. He speeds through his lecture so fast that you don't understand what or why he's doing what he is. Went to him during office hours, which only made things more confusing. He constantly says how easy it is for him and how smart he is. He's late, condescending, and not helpful. Don't take.

Good guy, fair, respectable But the lectures will have you doze off if you dont understand what is going on... You better do a lot of pre-reading before going to a lecture so you know what he is talking about...

I was doing very bad in this class. But I went to see him in his office and he really too time to help me. Logic is crazy hard until you get it, then it is obvious. If you don't go to class and don't keep up your screwed

Mulvihill is the definition of a "crazy uncle". He says little comments about what's on his mind as he teaches and it's hilarious. He explains things well, but does kind of look at you like you're stupid when you ask questions, even though he encourages questions. The course is cumulative though so you fall behind if you miss a class.

Gave a textbook that didn't provide many answers in the back making it difficult for you to ensure you understand not to mention we didn't get our grades back up until a week or two before the exam making it difficult for us to understand whether we're on the right track or not. I took this class for fun never again I learned nothing

Professor Mulvihill generally comes to class prepared and his textbook choice was cheap, however, he neglects to explain what the steps are for proofs, or give examples. He continuously says it is easy and that he knows how to do these problems but we don't and he doesn't help us to understand how to do it. If you want to learn, go elsewhere.
Great class, but hard. Prof has a great sense of humor.
I like this course alot. The prof has a dry sense of humor and really into the material.

Seems to be pretty interested in the course, however there are a LOT of red flags. His textbook and syllabus deviates significantly from the other classes, constantly late, and doesn't prepare powerpoints.

When it comes to Philosophy, you never really know what kinda prof you'll get. Mulvihill was a good prof who was also really funny in a "old guy who makes snide comments under his breath" kinda way. Also, his textbook is cheap and he does quizzes online that you take as many times as you want and it takes your highest quiz grade.

Despite other reviews on this page, he is actually an excellent prof. Very funny and extremely clear on what he's expecting for exams. His textbook is also only $25 and is very useful. He teaches you what you need to know to get a good mark and leaves all the useless stuff out.

THE WORST. STAY AWAY. SO CONFUSING. VERY UNCLEAR AND DISORGANIZED. WORST CLASS EVER TAKEN.  Every time he entered the class it looked like he was about to have a heart attack.  don't take this class. Run. away.

-His Textbook is really cheap compare to other prof, it's only $30 brand new -ALL the mid term and exam questions are similar to his textbook's exercise -He will go over the exercise with you in class -Basically, if you do all the exercises in his textbook, you will be fine.

Lectures were hard to follow and everywhere. Found myself better off to just do the notes from the book as well as the questions for the secretion. Basically taught myself the course and then showed up test days, as did half the class. Is clear with what will be on the tests though and sends out a rubric a week or two before hand.

We had three tests as well as final exams but you can drop the lowest mark which was nice. The textbook was all we need, everything that on the tests was in the textbook. The prof is hilarious in class, made a lot of joks and the grading criteria is very clear.
terrible

Extremely rude and unhelpful. Exams are incredibly difficult. I'm usually a good student, studied a lot, and still got less than a 60 on all of his exams. He doesn't respond to emails quickly and has no TAs. He also told me that asking for accomodations bc of an anxiety disorder was 'unacceptable'.  Lectures are very dry. A bad experience overall.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Very bad prof. There are not many positive things that I can say about the prof. The prof  uses the textbook a lot.
Not the greatest prof, goes off topic and gives terrible lectures.  However, he is very good-looking so that makes up for all the bad.
Well, his lecture is not mandatory. Sometimes, he uses a few questions in the textbook on his tests. There are three tests and a final throughout the semester.

He definitely improved throughout the semester he was however very rude to students during the first few classes. He only reeds from the textbook and basically just does the questions in the book in class with little added.
Some of the course was interesting but he did not really give any guidance when it came to papers.
Hes seems ok in person but he doesn't really offer you that much guidance and he is pretty unclear with what he expects of you. The course was reasonably interesting though.
Very vague and not really clear what he expects of you.
